jQuery.loadImg is a imgLoader.
$.loadImg loads img then cache it into the memory.
This may let you handle img loading easily.
works on jQuery 1.6.2.

added $.presetPreloader. (2011/08/16)
presetPreloader is useful when you use img rollover or css imgreplacement things.
This create only one img for each requested srcs using deferred.
Not documented yet, so check the demo to know how this works.

Usage:

$.loadImg('somewhere/img.png').then(function($img){
    $('body').append($img);
},function(error){
    alert(error.msg);
});


Demo:

http://dl.dropbox.com/u/268240/gitHubDemos/jQuery.loadImg/loadImg_w_flickr/index.html
http://dl.dropbox.com/u/268240/gitHubDemos/jQuery.loadImg/presetPreloader/index.html
